1. Initialise the NPM
    npm init -y
    - to setup npm in that directory
2. Install the Express Package
    npm i express
3. Write server application in index.js
4. To load an ES module, we have to include "type": "module" in the package.json.
5. Start server
    node index.js
        - make sure you end the server first

Tools to use to help you code in node:
Nodemon [https://www.npmjs.com/package/nodemon](Nodemon)
- automatically restars the node applicaiton when file changes in the directory are detected 
    npm install -g nodemon # or using yarn: yarn global add nodemon
    Then run index.js using nodemon
        nodemon index.js